{
  "texts": [
    "Analyzing the Jacobian matrix J = ∂Φ/∂x of the inner map, they identified three hallmark features of KAG:1.",
    "Zero rows: For a typical x, many hidden units become locally constant, with ∥∇ϕ i (x)∥ 2 ≈ 0 where the row index i depends on x.",
    "Minor concentration (MC):The distribution of k × k determinants (minors) of J has a large spike at zero, but is simultaneously heavy-tailed, with a few remarkably large values.",
    "(MC is measured by three observables called: Participation ratio, KL-divergence, and RR.)3.",
    "Alignment: The Jacobian structure exhibits non-generic alignment that is not preserved under random orthogonal rotations These signatures emerge without explicit regularization or architectural constraints-they appear to be a natural consequence of gradient-based optimization."
  ]
}